                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "The recent realizations of the quantum anomalous Hall effect (QAHE) in MnBiTe and MnBiTe benchmark the "
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        451,
                                        1585,
                                        2118,
                                        2111
                                    ],
                                    "type": "inline_equation",
                                    "content": "(\\mathrm{MnBi_6Te_4})(\\mathrm{Bi_2Te_3})_n"
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        451,
                                        1585,
                                        2118,
                                        2111
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": " family as a promising hotbed for further QAHE improvements. The family owes its potential to its ferromagnetically (FM) ordered MnBiTe septuple layers (SL). However, the QAHE realization is complicated in MnBiTe and MnBiTe due to the substantial antiferromagnetic (AFM) coupling between the SL. An FM state, advantageous for the QAHE, can be stabilized by interlacing the SL with an increasing number "
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        451,
                                        1585,
                                        2118,
                                        2111
                                    ],
                                    "type": "inline_equation",
                                    "content": "n"
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        451,
                                        1585,
                                        2118,
                                        2111
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": " of "
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        451,
                                        1585,
                                        2118,
                                        2111
                                    ],
                                    "type": "inline_equation",
                                    "content": "\\mathrm{Bi_2Te_3}"
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        451,
                                        1585,
                                        2118,
                                        2111
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": " layers. However, the mechanisms driving the FM state and the number of necessary QLs are not understood, and the surface magnetism remains obscure. Here, we demonstrate robust FM properties in MnBiTe10 "
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        451,
                                        1585,
                                        2118,
                                        2111
                                    ],
                                    "type": "inline_equation",
                                    "content": "n = 2"
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        451,
                                        1585,
                                        2118,
                                        2111
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": " with "
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        451,
                                        1585,
                                        2118,
                                        2111
                                    ],
                                    "type": "inline_equation",
                                    "content": "T_{c}\\approx 12\\mathrm{K}"
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        451,
                                        1585,
                                        2118,
                                        2111
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": " and establish their origin in the Mn/Bi intermixing phenomenon by a combined experimental and theoretical study. Our measurements reveal a magnetically intact surface with a large magnetic moment, and with FM properties similar to the bulk. Our investigation thus consolidates the MnBiTe10 system as perspective for the QAHE at elevated temperatures."
                                }
                            ]
